article.description: Campbell tops Delaware State in 70-55 win
article.headline: Campbell tops Delaware State in 70-55 win
article.linkText: Campbell tops Delaware State in 70-55 win
article.story: DOVER, Del. -- D.J. Mason scored 15 points and Kyre' Hamer added 12 more to lead Campbell to its second straight win of the season with a 70-55 victory over Delaware State on Wednesday night. Campbell (3-5) took control midway through the first half with a 24-2 breakaway run that included 3-pointers from Hamer, Luke Moyer, Curtis Phillips, Nehemiah Mabson and Andrew Ryan to build a 35-13 lead with 3:32 left before the break. Phillips finished with nine points and Reco McCarter had eight points and eight rebounds for the Camels, who shot 49 percent from the field and were 9 of 17 from 3-point range. The win snapped a 10-game road skid stretching back to last season for Campbell when playing on an opponent's home court. Amere May led Delaware State (4-5) with 28 points on 8-for-17 shooting from the floor and went 10 of 10 from the free throw line.
